This paper deals with codes designed for reliable communication over a noisy channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and communication theory (cs.COMM). The paper also discusses the behavior of MMSE and mutual information, which are important concepts in network information theory (cs.NI) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper provides a lower bound on the MMSE for finite length codes, which is related to machine learning and statistics (cs.LG).
